HEADWORD: Isonitroso-
<hw>I`so*ni*tro"so-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> +
<ets>nitroso</ets>-.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining form
(also used adjectively), signifying: Pertaining to, or designating, the
characteristic, nitrogenous radical, <chform>NOH</chform>, called the
<ex>isonitroso</ex> group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

